## 1. SAF-T XML SCHEMA STRUCTURE
(Use this to generate realistic sample fixture files for the demo)

### Root structure

```xml
<AuditFile xmlns="urn:StandardAuditFile-Taxation-Financial:NO"
           xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
           xsi:schemaLocation="...">

  <Header>
    <AuditFileVersion>1.10</AuditFileVersion>
    <AuditFileCountry>NO</AuditFileCountry>
    <AuditFileDateCreated>2024-01-31</AuditFileDateCreated>
    <SoftwareCompanyName>ComplianceCo</SoftwareCompanyName>
    <SoftwareID>AuditExport</SoftwareID>
    <SoftwareVersion>3.2.1</SoftwareVersion>
    <Company>
      <RegistrationNumber>987654321MVA</RegistrationNumber>
      <Name>Acme AS</Name>
      <Address>...</Address>
    </Company>
    <TaxAccountingBasis>A</TaxAccountingBasis>   <!-- A=accrual, C=cash -->
    <TaxEntity>Headquarters</TaxEntity>
    <FiscalYear>2023</FiscalYear>
    <StartDate>2023-01-01</StartDate>
    <EndDate>2023-12-31</EndDate>
    <CurrencyCode>EUR</CurrencyCode>
  </Header>

  <MasterFiles>

    <GeneralLedgerAccounts>
      <Account>
        <AccountID>1500</AccountID>
        <AccountDescription>Accounts Receivable</AccountDescription>
        <StandardAccountID>1500</StandardAccountID>
        <GroupingCategory>BS</GroupingCategory>  <!-- BS=balance sheet -->
        <GroupingCode>CurrentAssets</GroupingCode>
        <AccountType>Receivable</AccountType>
        <OpeningDebitBalance>45200.00</OpeningDebitBalance>
        <ClosingDebitBalance>51800.00</ClosingDebitBalance>
      </Account>
      <!-- ... more accounts ... -->
    </GeneralLedgerAccounts>

    <Customers>
      <Customer>
        <CustomerID>C-0001</CustomerID>
        <AccountID>1500</AccountID>
        <Name>Bjornstad Consulting</Name>
        <SelfBillingIndicator>0</SelfBillingIndicator>
        <OpeningDebitBalance>12000.00</OpeningDebitBalance>
        <ClosingDebitBalance>15400.00</ClosingDebitBalance>
      </Customer>
    </Customers>

    <Suppliers>
      <Supplier>
        <SupplierID>S-0001</SupplierID>
        <AccountID>2400</AccountID>
        <Name>Nordic Supply AS</Name>
        <OpeningCreditBalance>8800.00</OpeningCreditBalance>
        <ClosingCreditBalance>9200.00</ClosingCreditBalance>
      </Supplier>
    </Suppliers>

    <TaxTable>
      <TaxTableEntry>
        <TaxType>MVA</TaxType>
        <Description>Standard VAT 25%</Description>
        <TaxCode>3</TaxCode>
        <TaxPercentage>25.00</TaxPercentage>
        <Country>NO</Country>
      </TaxTableEntry>
      <TaxTableEntry>
        <TaxType>MVA</TaxType>
        <Description>Reduced VAT 15%</Description>
        <TaxCode>31</TaxCode>
        <TaxPercentage>15.00</TaxPercentage>
        <Country>NO</Country>
      </TaxTableEntry>
    </TaxTable>

  </MasterFiles>

  <GeneralLedgerEntries>
    <NumberOfEntries>12847</NumberOfEntries>
    <TotalDebit>4823100.50</TotalDebit>
    <TotalCredit>4823100.50</TotalCredit>   <!-- must balance! -->

    <Journal>
      <JournalID>SALES</JournalID>
      <Description>Sales Journal</Description>
      <JournalType>S</JournalType>
      <Transaction>
        <TransactionID>TXN-00001</TransactionID>
        <Period>1</Period>
        <PeriodYear>2023</PeriodYear>
        <TransactionDate>2023-01-15</TransactionDate>
        <Description>Invoice INV-2023-001</Description>
        <Line>
          <RecordID>1</RecordID>
          <AccountID>1500</AccountID>
          <Description>AR - Bjornstad Consulting</Description>
          <DebitAmount>
            <Amount>12500.00</Amount>
            <CurrencyCode>EUR</CurrencyCode>
          </DebitAmount>
        </Line>
        <Line>
          <RecordID>2</RecordID>
          <AccountID>3000</AccountID>
          <Description>Revenue - Services</Description>
          <CreditAmount>
            <Amount>10000.00</Amount>
            <CurrencyCode>EUR</CurrencyCode>
          </CreditAmount>
        </Line>
        <Line>
          <RecordID>3</RecordID>
          <AccountID>2700</AccountID>
          <Description>VAT Output 25%</Description>
          <CreditAmount>
            <Amount>2500.00</Amount>
            <CurrencyCode>EUR</CurrencyCode>
          </CreditAmount>
          <TaxInformation>
            <TaxType>MVA</TaxType>
            <TaxCode>3</TaxCode>
            <TaxPercentage>25.00</TaxPercentage>
            <TaxAmount>
              <Amount>2500.00</Amount>
              <CurrencyCode>EUR</CurrencyCode>
            </TaxAmount>
            <TaxBase>10000.00</TaxBase>
          </TaxInformation>
        </Line>
      </Transaction>
    </Journal>

  </GeneralLedgerEntries>

</AuditFile>
```

### Second format variant (for the format-detector feature)
A second common schema is the OECD generic SAF-T, which uses slightly different
element names: `<ns1:AuditFile>` with namespace prefix, `<n1:Header>`,
`<n1:MasterFiles>`, `<n1:GeneralLedgerEntries>`. The document type and period
can be detected from:
- `Header/AuditFileVersion` (e.g. "1.10" = Norwegian v1.10)
- `Header/AuditFileCountry` (e.g. "NO", "PT", "PL", "FR")
- `Header/StartDate` / `Header/EndDate` (fiscal period)
- Root namespace URI (urn:StandardAuditFile-Taxation-Financial:NO vs generic OECD)

For demo purposes, two fixtures are enough: one clean Norwegian SAF-T 1.10 file
and one with deliberate anomalies (missing TaxInformation on a taxable line,
debit != credit sum, CustomerID in a transaction that has no MasterFiles entry).

### Realistic file size note
In production, 500 MB+ SAF-T files arise from companies with 100,000+ journal
lines (high-volume retailers, manufacturers). Each Transaction node with 3-5
Line children might be ~800 bytes serialized. So 600,000 transactions ~ 480 MB.
For the demo, generate a data.js that simulates record counts at that scale
(~600k rows) while actually rendering a paginated 100k subset in the dashboard.

