## 2. FISCAL RECONCILIATION RULE CATEGORIES
(Basis for the 8-12 representative rules in the demo hero feature)

These categories map to how real SAF-T audit software (Deloitte, Sovos, KPMG)
structures validation suites. The 170+ rules the client mentions would be a
comprehensive enumeration within these categories.

### Category A: Structural Integrity
- A1  Schema validation: file validates against published XSD
- A2  Mandatory fields: no required element is empty or missing
- A3  Date consistency: all TransactionDate values fall within StartDate/EndDate
- A4  Period validity: Period (1-12) matches TransactionDate month

### Category B: Accounting Balance Rules
- B1  Trial balance: TotalDebit == TotalCredit (the foundational rule)
- B2  Transaction balance: sum(DebitAmount) == sum(CreditAmount) per transaction
- B3  Account continuity: OpeningBalance(period N) == ClosingBalance(period N-1)
- B4  GL rollup: sum of all Account.ClosingBalance == sum of all GL entry lines

### Category C: Master Data Cross-Reference
- C1  CustomerID referential integrity: every CustomerID in a transaction line
      must exist in MasterFiles/Customers
- C2  SupplierID referential integrity: same for suppliers
- C3  AccountID referential integrity: every AccountID used in a transaction
      must exist in GeneralLedgerAccounts
- C4  TaxCode validity: every TaxCode must exist in TaxTable

### Category D: VAT / Tax Reconciliation
- D1  VAT computation check: TaxAmount == TaxBase * (TaxPercentage / 100)
      within configurable rounding tolerance (default 0.02 EUR)
- D2  VAT account balance: sum of credit entries on VAT output accounts ==
      sum of TaxAmount on all outbound TaxInformation nodes
- D3  VAT period reconciliation: computed output VAT per period vs. declared VAT
      return totals (where return data is provided)
- D4  Reverse-charge detection: zero-rated lines with non-zero TaxBase and
      TaxCode flagged for review

### Category E: Completeness and Sequence
- E1  Invoice number gaps: detect missing numbers in a sequential invoice series
- E2  Transaction count: NumberOfEntries header value matches actual count
- E3  Duplicate TransactionIDs: no two transactions share an ID
- E4  Period transaction distribution: flag months with zero entries when prior
      year shows activity (potential omission)

### Category F: Anomaly / Risk Detection
- F1  Round-number concentration: flag transactions where Amount is an exact
      multiple of 1000, as a fraud-risk indicator
- F2  Unusual posting time: transactions posted outside business hours or on
      weekends (timestamp analysis)
- F3  Threshold-busting: line amounts just below approval thresholds (e.g. 4,950
      when threshold is 5,000)
- F4  Contra-account reversals: debit/credit flips within 48 hours on same
      account (potential error correction without proper documentation)

### Category G: Sub-ledger Reconciliation
- G1  AR sub-ledger to GL: sum of Customer.ClosingDebitBalance ==
      GL AccountID for AR closing balance
- G2  AP sub-ledger to GL: sum of Supplier.ClosingCreditBalance ==
      GL AccountID for AP closing balance
- G3  Bank/cash reconciliation: GL balance for cash accounts matches declared
      bank statement total

### Demo rule selection (8-12 representatives -- one per category):
Use: B1, B2, B3, C1, D1, D2, E1, E3, F1, F3, G1, G2
These cover the broadest set of client concerns and produce interesting
drill-down outputs in the demo.

