## 6. FIXTURE XML FOR DEMO (structural notes for demo-builder)

### saft-sample.xml (clean fixture -- all rules pass)
- 1 company, FY 2023, 5 journals (SALES, PURCHASES, PAYROLL, BANK, ADJ)
- 150 transactions total, all balanced, all accounts in MasterFiles
- 3 customers, 2 suppliers, 8 GL accounts
- VAT computations exact (25% on all taxable lines)
- Sequential invoice numbering (INV-2023-001 through INV-2023-089)
- NumberOfEntries in header matches actual count

### invoice-ledger-anomalies.xml (fixture with violations -- rules fail)
Intentionally seeded failures for demo rules:
- B1 violation: TotalCredit header value off by 500.00 (doesn't match line sum)
- C1 violation: TransactionID TXN-00042 references CustomerID C-9999 which
  has no MasterFiles entry
- D1 violation: line on TXN-00078 has TaxAmount 2600.00 but TaxBase 10000.00
  at 25% should be 2500.00 (off by 100.00, exceeds 0.02 tolerance)
- E1 violation: gap in invoice sequence (INV-2023-044 missing)
- F1 violation: three transactions with Amount exactly 5000.00 posted same day
- G1 violation: sum of Customer.ClosingDebitBalance (62800.00) != GL account
  1500 closing balance (58400.00) -- 4400 discrepancy

This gives the demo 6 rule violations across 6 categories, each with drillable
source records that the user can click into.

